Forgive us, friend, but there are no meals prepared at present, nor will there be until morning.	抱歉了,朋友,目前沒有準備好的餐點,得等到早上才有。
Forgive us, friend, but Shema is asleep.	抱歉了,朋友,舍瑪已經睡了。
Forgive us, friend, but Shema must prepare for the evening meal.  Perhaps you could wait until later for Shema to serve you.	抱歉了,朋友,舍瑪得準備晚餐了。或許你可以晚點再讓舍瑪為你服務。
There is also my nephew Scoree in the bazaar at the fountain plaza, who will be very happy to sell you something to eat.	我姪子史柯里也在噴泉廣場的市集裡,他會很樂意賣你點吃的。
If you will be seated, Shema will serve you.	只要您入座,舍瑪就會為您服務。
Shema will be with you shortly%s	舍瑪很快就會來為您服務%s
You are pleased at the delicious smells and delightful ambiance of the newly remodeled Katta's Tail Inn.  You give it three and a half stars.	這間剛翻修過的「卡塔尾旅店」香氣誘人、氣氛宜人,讓你相當滿意。你給它三顆半星的評價。
Your tea is on the table.	你的茶就在桌上。
Perhaps you should sit and ordered some.	或許你該坐下來點一些。
Aside from your water, you have nothing to drink.  You would no doubt receive tea with a meal.	除了你自己的水,你沒有別的飲料。點一份餐,想必會附上茶水。
You would undoubtedly receive tea with a meal, were you to order one.	如果你點一份餐,想必一定會附上茶水。
Your breakfast looks delicious.	你的早餐看起來很美味。
You have a wonderful meal.  There are numerous salads, the two main courses, fruit, hot mint tea, dessert, and all the bread you could want.  You feel stuffed and content.	你享用了一頓豐盛的美食。有多種沙拉、兩道主菜、水果、熱薄荷茶、甜點,還有吃不完的麵包。你感到心滿意足。
Fortunately, Heroes never get bellyaches.	幸好,英雄從不會鬧肚子痛。
Fortunately, your strenuous regimen as a Hero prevents you from looking as round as Abdulla.	幸好,英雄嚴格的鍛鍊讓你不會像阿布杜拉那樣圓滾滾的。
